		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Jany 26&#47;59</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear &#38; Respected Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I had the<lb/> honor of addressing you a few lines<lb/> on <date>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> November</date> last&#44; stating that<lb/> I had written <persName>Hon. Thos. Co. Florence</persName><lb/> enclosing your letter to him on <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Octo.</date><lb/> &#40;as I called on him several times without<lb/> succeeding in seeing him&#41; and that<lb/> I had not then &#40;&#38; have not yet&#41; heard<lb/> from in reply&#44; and would<lb/> not then have troubled you about<lb/> it but that I was so desirous<lb/> &#40;&#38; am still&#41; of obtaining the appointment<lb/> of commissioner for <placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Father would like you to<lb/> send him his bill of indebtedness</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>for the Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">By the way&#44; did <persName>L. Powers</persName><lb/> pay you for the Prayer Book<lb/> he got of you&#58; if not&#44; if you<lb/> will send me the Bill&#44; I will<lb/> endeavor to collect it for you here&#44;<lb/> from <persName>L. Y. Martin</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My Parents desire to be<lb/> kindly remembered.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I Remain Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">J. Solis Ritterband</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>224 Bowery</placeName></p>
		</body>
